lifecycles are managed by the OS


Lifecycle is a class that holds the informations about the lifecycle of a
a componenet !

this class has two enums 
- Event 
- State

"think of states as nodes in the graph and events as the edges between these nodes"

a class can monitor the component's lifecycle by implementating the 
DefaultLifecycleObserver!
and override the onResume/onPause

LifeCycleOwner is an interface that tell Android that his class
has a LifeCyclce
( it is a functional interface ! : getLifeCycle() )
